# GPU-fit tuning: Qwen3-Coder-Next UD-Q5_K_M on 2x R9700 (MACHINE=r9700-dual).
#
# Sourced by run-vulkan.sh AFTER models/qwen3-coder-next.env and BEFORE
# profiles/r9700-dual/default.env.
#
# All ~55 GiB of weights in VRAM => no CPU-MoE offload. The old 32K limit here
# was based on ~4x-overestimated KV math; actual cost (12 full-attention layers,
# 2 KV heads, head_dim 256) is ~12.75 KiB/token at q8_0, so 128K costs only
# ~1.6 GiB. V stays at the launcher's q8_0 default (the old q4_0 squeeze was
# unnecessary; K==V q8_0 keeps the fused Vulkan flash-attn path).
#   weights (UD-Q5_K_M)             55.2 GiB
#   KV @ 131,072 tok, q8_0 K+V       1.6 GiB
#   compute buffers @ ubatch 512    ~1.5 GiB
#   ------------------------------------------
#   total                          ~58.3 GiB / ~62 GiB VRAM  (margin ~3.5 GiB)
# 256K KV would only add 1.6 GiB more but leaves <2 GiB margin -- try it inline
# (CTX_SIZE=262144 ...) if you need it; drop UBATCH to 256 if load OOMs.
# For guaranteed 256K with headroom, use qwen3-coder-next-q4 (UD-Q4_K_XL).
: "${CTX_SIZE:=131072}"
: "${UBATCH:=512}"
